# AhaDiff

Use AhaDiff after meaningful code changes to turn the current diff into
verified learn-back artifacts.

Preferred commands:

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD`
- `ahadiff learn --staged`
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>`
- `ahadiff review`
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>`
- `ahadiff improve --rounds 1`
- `ahadiff serve`

Additional learn capture modes: `ahadiff learn --last`, `ahadiff learn --since
"2 hours ago"`, `ahadiff learn --unstaged`, and `ahadiff learn --patch FILE|-`.

## Boundaries

- Keep provider credentials in environment variables.
- Do not commit `.ahadiff/audit.private.jsonl`.
- Treat `.ahadiff/` as local state.
- Prefer verified claims with file-line evidence.
- Do not upload `.ahadiff/` artifacts to external services without explicit user consent.
